article.headline: Holy Cross 82, Army 51
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- Devin Brown scored 24 points and Holy Cross crushed Army 82-51 Wednesday night, extending the Crusaders' season-high winning streak to five games. R.J. Evans added 13 points for the Crusaders (14-13, 8-5 Patriot League), who had 10 players score as they avenged a Jan. 25 loss at Army. Holy Cross was in charge this time, opening on a 17-5 run in a game in which the Crusaders never trailed. They led by 19 points at the break and outscored the Black Knights 42-30 in the second half to seal it. Holy Cross outshot Army 51.7 percent (30 of 58) to 30.4 percent (17 of 56) from the floor and outrebounded the Black Knights 39-34. Josh Herbeck finished with 20 points to pace Army (12-16, 5-8), and Maxwell Lenox had 16. The Black Knights came in trying to win three straight games for the first time this season.
